  <title>GWeather.Location.prototype.find_nearest_city_full</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function find_nearest_city_full(lat: Number(gdouble), lon: Number(gdouble), func: <link xref="GWeather.FilterFunc">GWeather.FilterFunc</link>): <link xref="GWeather.Location">GWeather.Location</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for gweather_location_find_nearest_city_full()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Finds the nearest city to the passed latitude and
longitude, among the descendants of <code>loc</code>.</p>  <p>Supports the use of own filter function to filter out locations.
Geocoding should be done on the application side if needed.</p>  <p><code>loc</code> must be at most a <link xref="GWeather.LocationLevel"/>.adm2 location.
This restriction may be lifted in a future version.</p>
  <p>Since 3.12</p>
